    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I'm selling my trusty car and it\u2019s been such a gem to own. It\u2019s in really great shape and has been super reliable for all my daily errands and the occasional road trip. It drives smoothly, looks sharp, and I\u2019ve made sure to keep up with the basics so it\u2019s ready for its next adventure. If you're looking for a solid, well-loved ride that won't let you down, this is the one! I'd love for it to go to a good home, so feel free to reach out with any questions!",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant, delivering linear torque via Variocam Plus valve timing. Mated to a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle, the drivetrain remains tight with no significant synchro wear. Recent preventative maintenance includes an updated IMS bearing and a fresh rear main seal to ensure long-term mechanical integrity. The suspension retains its factory poise, utilizing MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup for precise turn-in and cornering stability. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina consistent with its enthusiast-driven history, the chassis remains rigid and the throttle response is sharp. A well-sorted driver for those seeking visceral rear-engine dynamics.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Reliable daily driver. Well-maintained engine. Clean interior. Minor exterior scuffs. All service records available. Tires in good shape.",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "Presenting a meticulously maintained BMW M3 that strikes the perfect balance between a spirited weekend driver and a reliable companion. The Interlagos Blue metallic paint retains a deep, mirror-like shine, though a few minor stone chips on the front fascia tell the story of enjoyable highway miles. Inside, the Novillo leather remains supple and free of tears, with only light bolstering wear on the driver\u2019s seat consistent with careful use. Every electronic feature, from the dual-zone climate control to the premium sound system, functions exactly as intended. Mechanically, this vehicle is sound; it has been serviced strictly on schedule, with a recent comprehensive fluid flush and a fresh set of performance tires installed recently. The engine pulls cleanly through the rev range, and the transmission shifts are crisp and certain. This is an honest, well-cared-for example that has been kept in a climate-controlled garage and is ready for its next enthusiast owner.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
